I followed the suggestions of mixing it up the day before and using proscuitto. I found it needed more cracked black pepper than I originally had thought, and I added some freshly chopped thyme too as it seemed bland. The day before we'd had figs broiled with a little gorgonzola and I much preferred that to this goat cheese.

Rating: 4
On the first night I served these appetizers, I scooped about a teaspoon of the mixture onto fig halves, then topped with a toasted walnut half. Everyone loved them. On the second night, I'd run out of figs but had lots of goat cheese mixture left. I served it with warm bread rolls and enjoyed it even more. The flavours were ultra smooth on the second day.

