Rating: 4
This is an absolutely fantastic recipe! An incredibly tasty and dramatic (and more importantly, EASY EASY EASY) appetizer to make. It can get a tad expensive (fresh figs are pricey in Canada!) if you're feeding a crowd, but definitely worth it for smaller gatherings. And like others have suggested, you should add a lot more cream to the mixture. Guaranteed to disappear quickly!

Rating: 3
Delicious and very easy. I agree with the reviewer from San Mateo that the consistency was more like a spread than a dip. My fix was to spread each fig half with the cheese mixture before serving. This took no time at all since I cut the proportions drastically for serving two as an appetizer. These lovely figs would also be good as a snack or dessert, in my opinion.

Rating: 3
